            <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><b>Related 
			Articles :</b></font><br>
              <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><ul><li><b><a href='http://originatortimes.com/content/templates/default.aspx?a=855&z=1'>Net Widens In Mortgage Fraud Case, Up To 13 More Could Be Charged</a></b><br>A federal prosecutor said Monday the U.S. government expects to charge as many as 13 more people in the mortgage fraud scheme orchestrated by Matthew Cox, a Tampa Heights mortgage broker now sought on identity theft and conspiracy charges filed by the U.S. Secret Service.<br></li><li><b><a href='http://originatortimes.com/content/templates/default.aspx?a=917&z=1'>Originator Allegedly Takes ABN Amro For Over $2 Million</a></b><br>Recently ABN Amro alleged in a civil suit filed in Federal court that Justin Stuckey an originator that operated Maximum Mortgage, Inc., in Fort Wayne, Indiana, together with Rex D. Wells, a real estate investor, and others orchestrated a complex scheme in which they enticed two seemingly innocent investors to purchase 149 properties using inflated appraisals and false terms that netted the perpetrators close to $2.5 million dollars.<br></li><li><b><a href='http://originatortimes.com/content/templates/default.aspx?a=940&z=1'>Five More Indicted in Mortgage Fraud Scheme</a></b><br>A federal indictment filed February 15, 2005 was recently unsealed. The indictment charges Darron Banks, Alan K. Banks, Mark A. Dean, Katrina L. Crenshaw and Galen J. Wade with wire fraud, bank fraud and conspiracy to commit wire fraud and bank fraud in connection with a $10M flipping scheme in the Dallas area.<br></li><li><b><a href='http://originatortimes.com/content/templates/default.aspx?a=970&z=1'>Three Arrested In Mortgage Fraud Schemes</a></b><br>Three people have been arrested for their alleged involvement in mortgage fraud schemes throughout Central and South Florida. Patricia C. Grant, 48, Edgar Grant, 70, and Geisha Morris, 22, were booked into the Orange County Jail this morning for allegedly falsifying a number of documents to obtain mortgages loans and properties in Orange, Broward, and Palm Beach counties.<br></li><li><b><a href='http://originatortimes.com/content/templates/default.aspx?a=1005&z=1'>Couple Convicted for Identity Theft and Mortgage Fraud</a></b><br>A husband and wife were convicted in federal court for identity theft, bank/mortgage fraud, credit card fraud and various other federal offenses after being tracked down by the victim.<br></li><li><b><a href='http://originatortimes.com/content/templates/default.aspx?a=1008&z=1'>Originator Accused of Multiple Frauds By Flagstar Bank</a></b><br>Recently, Flagstar Bank alleged in a civil suit filed in Federal court that DeAnn Johnson, an originator that was employed by Great Plains Mortgage Company, L.C., of Des Moines, Iowa, defrauded Flagstar by falsifying appraisals, supplying false income and asset information, and/or  engaging in a property flipping scheme during the financing of 9 properties.<br></li></ul></font> 
            </p>
